The paper deals with the vulnerability of OCR systems to adversarial attacks, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the impact of these attacks on natural language processing (NLP) applications, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper discusses the security implications of these attacks, which is related to computer security (cs.CR) and adversarial machine learning (cs.AI).
